subject:

GOD HELPS THE FALLEN (read 145:13-21)
===================================================================
verse:

The Lord helps the fallen and lifts up those bent beneath
their loads. All eyes look up to You for help: You give them
their food as they need it. (Ps. 145:14, 15)

===================================================================
reflection:

Sometimes our burdens are more then we can bear, and we
wonder how we can go on. God is, able to lift us up because
(1) His greatness is beyond discovery (145:3): (2) He does
mighty acts for each generation (145:4): (3) He is full of
mighty splendor and majesty (145:5): (4) He does awe
inspiring deeds (145:5, 6): (5) He is righteous (Ps. 145:7):
(6) He is kind, merciful, patient, and compassionate (145:8,
9): (7) He rules over an everlasting Kingdom (145:13): (8)
He is the source of all our daily needs: (Ps. 145:15, 16):
(9) He is righteous and kind in all His dealings (145:17):
God is ready to lift you up.

===================================================================
prayer:

Lord God, You are great beyond all understanding, doing
mighty acts for every generation with splendor and majesty.
Your righteousness, kindness, mercy, and compassion never
fail, and Your everlasting kingdom sustains all who call
upon You. You provide for every living thing and lift up
those who are bowed down. May we find strength and hope in
Your unfailing love and be encouraged by Your constant care.
Amen. (AI)

===================================================================
